    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1973-03-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1973-03-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="20"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d20">
                <head>20. Message From President <persName corresp="#p_NRM1" type="from"
                        >Nixon</persName> to Japanese Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_TK1"
                        type="to">Tanaka</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d20fn1">Source: National Archives, <persName
                            corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName> Presidential Materials, NSC Files,
                            <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName> Office Files, Box 53,
                        Country Files, Europe, Monetary Crisis, March 1973. Top Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1973-03-03">March 3, 1973</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">Dear Mr. Prime Minister:</p>
                <p>I have today received a letter from Chancellor <persName corresp="#p_BW1"
                        >Brandt</persName> informing me that the European countries are planning to
                    develop a proposal to deal with the current currency crisis.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d20fn2">
                        <ref target="#d15">Document 15.</ref>
                    </note> I want you to know that I have replied to Chancellor <persName
                        corresp="#p_BW1">Brandt</persName> and have also written to Prime Minister
                        <persName corresp="#p_HE1">Heath</persName> saying that any solution to the
                    currency crisis should be developed through full consultations with the United
                    States and with Japan<note n="3" xml:id="d20fn3">
                        <ref target="#d18">Documents 18</ref> and <ref target="#d19"
                        >19</ref>.</note>—a point we had previously made orally to Prime Minister
                        <persName corresp="#p_HE1">Heath</persName>.</p>
                <p>We will be prepared to exchange views with you on this subject.</p>
                <p>With kind regards.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_NRM1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Richard Nixon</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                    <note n="4" xml:id="d20fn4">Printed from a copy that bears <persName
                            corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName>’s typed signature with an indication
                        that he signed the original.</note>
                </closer>
            </div>
